<!-- Solutions -->
<section class="section bg-cream">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="section-header centered">
            <span class="section-eyebrow">Applications</span>
            <h2>Where We Solve Effluent Challenges</h2>
            <p>From small onsite systems to large municipal land application sites, DripSmart's engineered solutions meet local, state, and federal disposal requirements.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="three-col-grid">
            <div class="info-card">
                <div class="info-card-icon">🏠</div>
                <h3>Onsite Septic Systems</h3>
                <p>Replace failing drain fields with long-lasting drip dispersal systems. Ideal for challenging soils, small lots, and setback-constrained sites.</p>
                <ul class="check-list">
                    <li>NSF 245/61 certified products</li>
                    <li>Anti-siphon check valves</li>
                    <li>Soil loading rate calculations provided</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="info-card">
                <div class="info-card-icon">🏭</div>
                <h3>Municipal Land Application</h3>
                <p>Large-scale sub-surface drip application of Class A or Class B reclaimed water on agricultural land, buffer zones, and public green space.</p>
                <ul class="check-list">
                    <li>High flow driplines up to 2 GPH/emitter</li>
                    <li>Anti-intrusion root barriers</li>
                    <li>SCADA-compatible control systems</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="info-card">
                <div class="info-card-icon">🌾</div>
                <h3>Agricultural Reuse</h3>
                <p>Apply reclaimed water directly to crop root zones with zero runoff, zero aerial spray, and full compliance with ag water reuse standards.</p>
                <ul class="check-list">
                    <li>Title 22 compliant systems</li>
                    <li>Nutrient credit tracking software</li>
                    <li>Crop-specific loading rate guidance</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="info-card">
                <div class="info-card-icon">🏕️</div>
                <h3>RV Parks &amp; Remote Sites</h3>
                <p>Compact, automated drip dispersal for remote facilities, campgrounds, and rural commercial properties where centralized sewer is unavailable.</p>
                <ul class="check-list">
                    <li>Systems sized 200–50,000 GPD</li>
                    <li>Filter &amp; pump assembly included</li>
                    <li>Alarm and telemetry monitoring</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="info-card">
                <div class="info-card-icon">🏗️</div>
                <h3>Food Processing Facilities</h3>
                <p>High-strength process wastewater from food &amp; beverage operations is nutrient-rich. Our systems turn that into a valuable soil amendment while meeting permit limits.</p>
                <ul class="check-list">
                    <li>High-flow emitter options</li>
                    <li>Clog-resistant anti-siphon drippers</li>
                    <li>BOD/TSS pre-treatment guidance</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="highlight-card">
                <div class="info-card-icon">📋</div>
                <h3>Permitting &amp; Compliance Support</h3>
                <p>Our engineering team has assisted with permitting in over 35 states. We provide hydraulic calculations, loading rate reports, and regulatory documentation packages.</p>
                <a href="/contact" class="btn-outline-dark mt-md">Request Engineering Support</a>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

