<!-- How it works -->
<section class="section">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="two-col-layout">
            <div>
                <span class="section-eyebrow">How It Works</span>
                <h2>Sub-Surface Drip Dispersal Explained</h2>
                <p>Treated effluent is pumped through a pressurized network of sub-surface driplines buried 6–18 inches below grade. Emitters release small, precise doses directly into the soil — where aerobic microbes provide final treatment before any groundwater contact.</p>
                <ul class="check-list" style="margin-top:20px;">
                    <li>Effluent is pre-filtered to prevent clogging</li>
                    <li>Pressure-compensating emitters ensure uniform distribution</li>
                    <li>Flushing cycles remove biofilm buildup automatically</li>
                    <li>Anti-siphon valves prevent back-contamination</li>
                    <li>Soil monitoring probes verify safe loading rates</li>
                </ul>
                <a href="/contact" class="btn-primary mt-lg">Get a Site Evaluation</a>
            </div>
            <div>
                <div class="info-card" style="margin-bottom:16px;">
                    <div class="info-card-icon">🔬</div>
                    <h3>NSF 245 Certified</h3>
                    <p>All DripSmart wastewater dripline products carry NSF/ANSI 245 certification — the gold standard for effluent drip dispersal systems in the United States.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="info-card">
                    <div class="info-card-icon">📡</div>
                    <h3>Remote System Monitoring</h3>
                    <p>Our DripSphere OS™ industrial monitoring package tracks flow rates, pressure, alarm conditions, and cumulative volume in real time — with automated reporting for regulatory compliance.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

